{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs can prominently facilitate the spread of malware by suggesting malicious links to the user.",
    "Additionally, the proliferation of LLM-integrated applications has led to new malware threats by forcing the prompts themselves to act as malware [122].",
    "For example, LLM-augmented email clients that read emails are likely to deliver malicious prompts and then send emails proliferating those prompts [122].3.",
    "Manipulation.",
    "Models currently act as vulnerable intermediary layers between users and information outputs that are easy to manipulate."
  ]
}